Kiri - A tiny C++ source code assistant


What is Kiri?

Kiri is a minimal software solution designed to assist in the process of C++
project development by taking on responsibility for clean source code.


What does Kiri do?

Kiri is capable of scanning C++ source files and correcting human errors in
terms of code formatting, include directives or forward declarations. When run
in daemon mode, Kiri can watch for changes in the source tree and automatically
apply changes if necessary.


